/4/22/Neider-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For quarterback-turned-wide receiver John Neider, he's either a wide receiver who once played quarterback, or a quarterback who is now playing wide receiver.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/22/Neider-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/22/Neider-Main.jpg"><media:title>John Neider</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/22/Neider-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 13:25:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59035</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kellogg Announces Signing of Kennedy Harris</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/22/womens-basketball-kellogg-announces-signing-of-kennedy-harris</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/22/womens-basketball-kellogg-announces-signing-of-kennedy-harris</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WBB Hope Coliseum" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/10/WBB_Stadium_Photo__5_.JPG" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University women's basketball head coach Mark Kellogg has announced the addition of Kennedy Harris (Hampton, Va. / George Mason / Hampton HS) to a grant-in-aid for the 2026-27 academic year.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/10/WBB_Stadium_Photo__5_.JPG" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/10/WBB_Stadium_Pho