14.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/21/BSBvsPITT-35.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/21/BSBvsPITT-35.jpeg"><media:title>Armani Guzman</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/21/BSBvsPITT-35.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 21:39:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59030</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kellogg Announces Signing of Nylah Wilson</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/21/womens-basketball-kellogg-announces-signing-of-nylah-wilson</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/21/womens-basketball-kellogg-announces-signing-of-nylah-wilson</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WBB Hope Coliseum" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/6/WBB_Stadium_Photo__8_.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University women's basketball head coach Mark Kellogg has announced the addition of Nylah Wilson (Chester, Va. / Pitt / IMG Academy) to a grant-in-aid for the 2026-27 academic year.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/6/WBB_Stadium_Photo__8_.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/6/WBB_Stadium_Photo__8_.jpg"><media:title>WBB Hope Coliseum</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/6/WBB_Stadium_Photo__8_.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 12:56:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59029</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Rifle Invited to White House</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/21/west-virginia-rifle-invited-to-white-house</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/21/west-virginia-rifle-invited-to-white-house</guid><category>Rifle</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WVU NCAA National Championship Team Photo" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/21/DSC02500_3.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the third time in West Virginia University history and the first time since 2017, a Mountaineer athletic team will visit the White House and meet with the President of the United States for NCAA Champions Day.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/21/DSC02500_3.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/21/DSC02500_3.jpg"><media:title>WVU NCAA National Championship Team Photo</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/21/DSC02500_3.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 11:43:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>8</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59028</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Set to Host Backyard Brawl</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/20/baseball-mountaineers-set-to-host-backyard-brawl</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/20/baseball-mountaineers-set-to-host-backyard-brawl</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup vs. Pitt 2026" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/20/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Pitt.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 12 West Virginia University baseball team returns to Kendrick Family Ballpark to take on Pitt in this year's lone edition of the Backyard Brawl. First pitch on Tuesday, April 21, is scheduled for 6:30 p.m.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Pitt.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Pitt.jpg"><media:title>Matchup vs. Pitt 2026</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Pitt.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 17:08:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59027</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>